**Overall Meaning:**

"May my mind be filled with auspicious thoughts, that which goes far for the waking and in the same way for the sleeping, the far-reaching light, the one light of all lights."

**Explanation:**

This verse highlights the omnipresence and constant presence of the divine, regardless of our state of consciousness.  It mentions that the divine is always present, whether we are awake or asleep, and this divine light is the source of all other lights, the ultimate reality that transcends our limited perception. The verse expresses a desire for the mind to be attuned to this ever-present divine light, even when we are not consciously aware of it. 
